<paragraph blockId="6.[264,1324,284,1313]" box="[312,1044,1087,1113]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Etymology. The specific epithet derives from the acute cercus.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[264,1324,284,1313]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Comments. This new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Yang" authorityName="Yang" box="[811,1195,1127,1153]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysotimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicicurvatus">
<emphasis box="[811,1127,1127,1152]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Chrysotimus apicicurvatus</emphasis>
Yang
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion country="China" name="Zhejiang" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Zhejiang</collectingRegion>
, but may be separated from the latter by 6 dc, 5–6 irregularly paired acr, and enlarged hypandrium. In 
<taxonomicName box="[465,664,1207,1232]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysotimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicicurvatus">
<emphasis box="[465,664,1207,1232]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">C. apicicurvatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it has 5 dc and no acr, and the hypandrium is not enlarged (Yang, 2001).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[264,1324,284,1313]" box="[312,613,1287,1313]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Distribution. 
<collectingRegion box="[468,609,1287,1313]" country="China" name="Guangdong" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Guangdong</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
